   教授簡介 
 【Introduction】

　　I was born in Hong Kong in 1960, earned my Ph. D Degree in the National Taiwan University in 1996, and promoted to be a full professor in 2002. My main specialty is the study of East Asian humanities, focusing on the theory of Semantics, Chinese intellectual history and Yijing (The Classic of Changes). I have written five books, edited nine research anthologies and published more than forty research articles in Chinese, English, Japanese and Korean. 

　　I acted as the director of a subproject of the “Pursuing for Excellence Project” of the Ministry of Education 2000-2004. I also acted as a group leader of the NTU Center for the Study of East Asian Civilizations 2002-2005. In 2006, in conjunction with scholars from various countries, I established the “Forum for the Studies of Canonical Texts and Their Interpretations,” under the auspices of which we have already held several international symposiums and published five anthologies.

　　I had visited the University of Washington (Seattle), Peking University, Tsinghua University, Hokkaido University and National University of Singapore (Asia Research institute) as senior visiting scholar. Visitors are welcome to two forum webpage: http://eastasia.csie.org/yiforum/, http://eastasia.csie.org/fsctt/zh/.   

